<font color="#FF0000">WHY ARE WE HERE?</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec 16 22:25:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Sanity is a necessary for anyone.  The unfortunate character we suffer is the intense frustration of being thrust into an insane situation.  Faced by the dilemma of protecting our basic values, honor, and integrity and additionally being asked to keep the site alive and accepting of new comers we were running an emotional gauntlet.  The situations created sometimes had a price to high to pay and we chose to fight with the same intense emotional commitment that creates the heart of the warrior.  Not an esoteric statement for those who understand.<br><br>
In an effort to maintain our own sanity and sense of honor we bonded the same way many combat veterans bonded during their struggle in Vietnam.  It is not something I am ashamed of nor will I ever apologize for this exclusivity that others feel we project.  It is who we are not what we became.  It should be a positive statement to be honest.  Honesty is what will make this site survive.  If it can't stand the honesty of those that post here then it has no real purpose.<br><br>
I will embrace the ideas of an honest man because he has integrity whether he holds my beliefs or not.  With the same tenacity I will despise a charlatan.  A matter of choice.  I would always choose to leave before I would present my self as something I am not.<br><br>
Honor and integrity have a place here.  I do not feel it is too much to ask.<br>

